          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make the almond cream",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Beat the {{unsalted-butter}} and {{caster-sugar}} together until pale. Beat in the {{eggs}} (cream amount) one at a time. Fold in the {{almond-flour}}, {{plain-flour}}, {{almond-extract}}, and {{vanilla-extract}}. Chill for at least 30 minutes until firm.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Assemble and bake, 30 to 35 minutes",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Preheat the oven to 200°C fan. Roll the {{puff-pastry}} and cut two 22 cm discs. Place one disc on a lined baking tray. Spread the chilled almond cream over the base disc, leaving a 2 cm border. Brush the border with beaten {{eggs}} (wash amount). Place the second disc on top and press the edges firmly to seal. Crimp the edge with a fork or the back of a spoon. Chill for 20 minutes. Brush the top with egg wash. Score the top surface in a spiral fan pattern with a sharp knife, going no deeper than 2 mm. Make a small hole in the centre for steam to escape. Bake for 30 to 35 minutes until risen, deep golden, and firm. Cool on a rack for at least 15 minutes before serving warm.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
